
Overview of adj choleric

The adj choleric has 3 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                      
1. choleric -- (easily moved to anger; "men of the choleric type take to kicking and smashing"- H.G.Wells)
2. choleric, irascible, hotheaded, hot-tempered, quick-tempered, short-tempered -- (quickly aroused to anger; "a hotheaded commander")
3. choleric, irascible -- (characterized by anger; "a choleric outburst"; "an irascible response")
